by.schepov.motordepot.builder

Interface Builder<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the element to be build by the builder
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBuilder, CarBuilder, CarNameBuilder, OrderBuilder, RequestBuilder, ResultSetCarBuilder, ResultSetCarNameBuilder, ResultSetOrderBuilder, ResultSetRequestBuilder, ResultSetUserBuilder, UserBuilder

    public interface Builder<T>
    The interface providing methods of a classic builder. The classes implementing this interface provide a convenient way to construct objects with many fields and help to avoid using constructors with a large number of parameters.
    See Also:
    AbstractBuilder, CarBuilder, ResultSetCarBuilder, CarNameBuilder, ResultSetCarNameBuilder, OrderBuilder, ResultSetOrderBuilder, RequestBuilder, ResultSetRequestBuilder, UserBuilder, ResultSetUserBuilder

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T build()
      The method returns the object constructed using other methods of Builder implementation called after the latest reset() call.
      void reset()
      Refreshes the object inside the builder.

    • Method Detail

      • reset

        void reset()
        Refreshes the object inside the builder. Should be called before constructing an object using other methods of Builder implementations in order to avoid getting an object with unwanted field values.

      • build

        T build()
        The method returns the object constructed using other methods of Builder implementation called after the latest reset() call. This method does not refresh the object inside the builder.
        Returns:
        the object constructed after the latest reset() call
